Michael D. Rumbolz  Chief Executive Officer, President and Director, Everi Holdings Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships63$1,258,579As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Michael D. Rumbolz, also known as Mike, has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Everi Holdings Inc. since May 10, 2016. Mr. Rumbolz has been the Owner and Managing Director of Acme Gaming LLC since July 2001. He has over 20 years of experience in the gaming industry. He held various executive positions with Trump Hotels & Casino Resorts. He served as the Interim Chief Executive Officer and Interim President at Everi Holdings Inc. from February 16, 2016 ... to May 10, 2016. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the Board of Cash Systems, Inc. from January 2005 to August 2008 and also served as its President since April 2005. He served as an Independent Consultant to Global Cash Access Holdings, Inc. (GCA). He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Anchor Gaming from 1995 to 2000. He served as the President and Managing Director of Windsor Casino Limited at the time of its opening. He served as the Chief Deputy Attorney General of the State of Nevada since 1983. He served as the Senior Attorney for the Nevada gaming regulatory system. His activities included providing legal advice to all divisions of the State Gaming Control Board and Nevada Gaming Commission. He served as Director of Corporate Development for Circus Circus Enterprises Inc. from 1992 to June 1995. He has been the Chairman of Employers Holdings, Inc. since June 7, 2016. He served as the Chairman of the Nevada Gaming Control Board, a Member since 1985 and Executive Director for the agency from June 1987 to December 1988. He served as Vice Chairman and Director of Casino Data Systems from March 2000 to July 2001. He has been a Director for Everi Holdings Inc. since August 2010, Employers Holdings, Inc., since April 2005 and EIG Inc. since April 2005. He has been an Independent Director for Employers Holdings, Inc., since April 2005. He serves as a Director of Employers Group, Inc. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Poydras Street Capital LLC. He serves as a Trustee of The Nathan Adelson Hospice. He served as a Director of Poydras Gaming Finance Corp. until March 17, 2015, Affinity Gaming Inc. from December 31, 2010 to April 1, 2013, EICN from January 2000 to March 2007, Cash Systems Inc. since January 2005 and ECIC and its predecessor from August 2002 to May 2004. He received a BA degree in Political Science with distinction from the University of Nevada, Las Vegas and a J.D. degree from the University of Southern California, Gould School of Law.Read Full Background




